WEBVTT

00:00:15.042 --> 00:00:19.500
"November 5, 2024"  "Floor 22: Lake Outside Coral City"

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:38.000
Catch anything?

00:00:43.292 --> 00:00:45.708
Sorry to scare you...

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:54.250
My name is Nishida.

00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:56.125
In the game, I'm a fisherman.

00:00:56.500 --> 00:01:02.042
In Japan, I was head of the network security
division for Toto High-Speed Internet.

00:01:02.042 --> 00:01:03.375
I'm Kirito.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.292
Didn't Toto High-Speed Internet...

00:01:06.292 --> 00:01:07.208
Yes.

00:01:07.208 --> 00:01:10.708
I oversaw network security
for this game.

00:01:15.958 --> 00:01:16.958
It's big!

00:01:18.250 --> 00:01:19.750
Piece of cake!

00:01:24.250 --> 00:01:25.792
That was awesome.

00:01:25.792 --> 00:01:26.792
Thank you.

00:01:27.417 --> 00:01:31.208
I can catch these things,
but I can't cook them.

00:01:31.208 --> 00:01:34.208
I'd love to stew them
or make sashimi,

00:01:34.208 --> 00:01:36.875
but I don't have any soy sauce.

00:01:37.417 --> 00:01:40.500
Maybe baked with soy sauce.

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:44.750
--Or maybe with radishes and soy sauce...
--I may be able to help with that.

00:01:45.917 --> 00:01:49.417
What?

00:02:01.417 --> 00:02:05.833
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:02:06.167 --> 00:02:11.667
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:22.542
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:02:22.875 --> 00:02:27.875
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:02:28.208 --> 00:02:32.583
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:02:32.917 --> 00:02:35.292
<i>Out of control</i>

00:02:35.625 --> 00:02:40.875
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:02:41.250 --> 00:02:46.083
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:02:46.417 --> 00:02:52.583
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:02:52.917 --> 00:02:56.542
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:02:56.875 --> 00:03:01.833
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:03:02.167 --> 00:03:07.833
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:11.208
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:03:11.542 --> 00:03:16.917
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:03:20.083 --> 00:03:24.042
"Edge of Hell's Abyss"

00:03:25.500 --> 00:03:28.333
That was wonderful!

00:03:28.542 --> 00:03:32.125
I had no idea you could get
soy sauce in this world.

00:03:32.958 --> 00:03:34.458
It's homemade.

00:03:34.458 --> 00:03:37.458
--Take some with you if you'd like.
--Really?

00:03:37.458 --> 00:03:40.167
I appreciate that!

00:03:41.333 --> 00:03:44.750
But anyway, your fishing skill
must be very high.

00:03:45.500 --> 00:03:48.542
Kirito's never managed
to bring anything home.

00:03:50.708 --> 00:03:54.333
The lakes around here
are too hard!

00:03:54.333 --> 00:03:57.458
No, that isn't really true.

00:03:57.458 --> 00:04:02.583
The only difficult one is the big lake
where you were fishing.

00:04:03.917 --> 00:04:06.625
Why design it like that?

00:04:06.625 --> 00:04:08.583
Yes, excellent question!

00:04:08.917 --> 00:04:10.667
In that lake

00:04:11.667 --> 00:04:13.542
there's a guardian, you see.

00:04:13.542 --> 00:04:14.958
--A guardian?
--A guardian?

00:04:14.958 --> 00:04:16.292
Yes...

00:04:16.292 --> 00:04:20.542
I've had it strike
several times myself.

00:04:21.167 --> 00:04:25.167
But it was so powerful it dragged
my pole away altogether.

00:04:27.125 --> 00:04:31.083
And so, I'd like to ask
something of you.

00:04:37.292 --> 00:04:42.625
I don't mind fishing for a guardian, but is it
possible to switch with a fishing pole?

00:04:42.917 --> 00:04:45.167
If anyone can, you can.

00:04:49.708 --> 00:04:52.208
If you catch it, then what?
Will you keep it?

00:04:52.208 --> 00:04:54.042
Can you keep something like that?

00:04:59.958 --> 00:05:02.167
He was a funny guy, wasn't he?

00:05:02.792 --> 00:05:05.958
I was surprised when you brought
him here with no warning.

00:05:08.417 --> 00:05:12.625
There are so many people leading
ordinary lives in this world...

00:05:13.417 --> 00:05:16.333
Since we can fight
on the front lines,

00:05:16.333 --> 00:05:19.542
we have a responsibility
to them, don't we?

00:05:21.167 --> 00:05:22.208
For me...

00:05:22.750 --> 00:05:28.208
...getting stronger was mainly for
the sake of my own survival.

00:05:32.375 --> 00:05:37.042
I think that lots of people expect
great things from you now...

00:05:37.792 --> 00:05:39.458
Including me.

00:05:42.167 --> 00:05:43.458
Yeah...

00:05:43.458 --> 00:05:48.000
I promised that I'd save everyone.

00:05:50.250 --> 00:05:53.750
But for just a little longer...

00:05:54.625 --> 00:05:55.625
Yeah.

00:06:00.417 --> 00:06:02.417
"You can do it, Nishida!"

00:06:02.417 --> 00:06:05.042
"Catch the guardian!"

00:06:05.042 --> 00:06:06.292
Seriously?

00:06:06.958 --> 00:06:09.542
Everyone knew about that fish, I see!

00:06:11.958 --> 00:06:13.292
And now,

00:06:13.958 --> 00:06:17.167
it's time for the day's main event.

00:06:17.167 --> 00:06:18.750
We've been waiting for this!

00:06:18.750 --> 00:06:21.125
Kirito, let's do this.

00:06:21.375 --> 00:06:22.375
Sure.

00:06:25.458 --> 00:06:27.875
How big is this thing?

00:06:28.708 --> 00:06:30.750
Here we go...

00:06:54.125 --> 00:06:56.208
Um, isn't that it?

00:06:56.208 --> 00:06:57.417
Not yet.

00:06:58.958 --> 00:07:00.583
N-Nishida...

00:07:00.583 --> 00:07:02.708
Hang on. Not yet.

00:07:04.875 --> 00:07:06.042
Now!

00:07:06.042 --> 00:07:07.292
I've got it!

00:07:08.542 --> 00:07:10.042
Here!

00:07:10.042 --> 00:07:11.542
S-Switch--

00:07:16.375 --> 00:07:19.833
Damn it! You little...

00:07:22.875 --> 00:07:23.875
I see it!

00:07:31.375 --> 00:07:33.000
Okay, I've got this...

00:07:35.417 --> 00:07:37.500
Wh-What? Hey!

00:07:39.333 --> 00:07:40.333
Ow...

00:07:43.875 --> 00:07:45.333
Kirito!

00:07:45.750 --> 00:07:47.583
Look out!

00:07:48.667 --> 00:07:49.750
For what?

00:08:03.417 --> 00:08:06.500
Th-Th-That's unfair!
Don't run away and leave me...

00:08:06.875 --> 00:08:08.042
Kirito!

00:08:10.792 --> 00:08:12.542
It's running on land.

00:08:12.542 --> 00:08:14.208
Is it a lungfish?

00:08:14.208 --> 00:08:15.417
Kirito!

00:08:15.417 --> 00:08:17.583
Don't be so nonchalant!

00:08:17.583 --> 00:08:19.125
Make a run for it!

00:08:19.125 --> 00:08:21.375
Ah, right.

00:08:21.375 --> 00:08:23.250
Oh, fine...

00:08:26.833 --> 00:08:28.458
Missus, run!

00:08:28.458 --> 00:08:30.167
She'll be fine.

00:08:31.375 --> 00:08:33.375
Kirito, your wife!

00:08:35.125 --> 00:08:36.625
Missus!

00:08:48.958 --> 00:08:52.458
A-Amazing!

00:08:52.917 --> 00:08:54.667
You're Asuna, right?

00:08:54.667 --> 00:08:55.917
What are you doing here?

00:08:56.542 --> 00:08:57.917
I'm a fan!

00:08:57.917 --> 00:08:59.917
Can I shake your hand too?

00:09:01.375 --> 00:09:02.583
Good work.

00:09:05.292 --> 00:09:06.833
Heathcliff?

00:09:15.167 --> 00:09:17.917
All right! You've moped
long enough.

00:09:17.917 --> 00:09:21.417
But it's only been two weeks...

00:09:21.417 --> 00:09:26.333
If he's summoning us to the front lines
during our vacation, it must be a big deal.

00:09:26.333 --> 00:09:28.417
True, but still...

00:09:29.250 --> 00:09:31.333
Let's at least hear
what he has to say.

00:09:31.708 --> 00:09:33.542
Come on, it's time.

00:09:40.208 --> 00:09:42.458
Let's get this out of the
way and come back.

00:09:42.458 --> 00:09:44.000
Right.

00:09:46.875 --> 00:09:48.375
Thanks for seeing us off.

00:09:48.375 --> 00:09:49.500
"November 7, 2024"
"Floor 22: Coral Teleport Gate Plaza"

00:09:49.500 --> 00:09:52.625
"November 7, 2024"
"Floor 22: Coral Teleport Gate Plaza"
We didn't spend much time together, but it was fun.

00:09:52.625 --> 00:09:55.875
Yes, it was a good experience for me.

00:09:56.458 --> 00:09:58.708
Actually, before meeting you,

00:09:58.708 --> 00:10:05.000
I'd thought those working to clear
the game were in a different world.

00:10:05.750 --> 00:10:08.542
I've been trapped in here
for two years.

00:10:08.542 --> 00:10:12.500
Even if I make it back somehow,
I don't know if I can return to my old job.

00:10:12.833 --> 00:10:16.583
It's possible that deep down inside,

00:10:16.583 --> 00:10:19.542
I might've already given up on escape.

00:10:19.833 --> 00:10:24.000
And convinced myself I was better off
here with a fishing rod in my hand.

00:10:24.417 --> 00:10:26.583
It's pretty sad.

00:10:26.583 --> 00:10:27.708
No...

00:10:27.708 --> 00:10:29.583
No, that isn't...

00:10:29.583 --> 00:10:30.667
Me too.

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:35.875
At first, I thought the same thing.

00:10:35.875 --> 00:10:37.958
I spent every night crying alone.

00:10:38.625 --> 00:10:41.125
It felt like every day
that passed here

00:10:41.125 --> 00:10:44.792
stole another piece
of my real life away.

00:10:46.250 --> 00:10:49.833
After I cried, I'd go and
fight as hard as I could.

00:10:50.250 --> 00:10:52.458
My only thought was of winning,

00:10:52.458 --> 00:10:55.000
moving forward,
and getting stronger.

00:10:55.833 --> 00:11:00.125
But then, I saw someone napping
in the shade at the plaza.

00:11:01.167 --> 00:11:02.875
It made me so mad.

00:11:03.333 --> 00:11:06.083
I told him to stop wasting his time.

00:11:06.875 --> 00:11:10.750
And he replied that it was
Aincrad's best season,

00:11:10.750 --> 00:11:13.083
and its best weather setting too.

00:11:13.083 --> 00:11:16.750
So it would be a waste to enter
a dungeon on such a day.

00:11:17.667 --> 00:11:20.417
Then I tried lying down too,

00:11:20.417 --> 00:11:21.958
and I slept like a baby.

00:11:23.375 --> 00:11:26.958
When I awoke, it was evening,
and he was giving me a look of disbelief...

00:11:27.750 --> 00:11:32.417
But as we partied up together,
I realized something.

00:11:33.042 --> 00:11:36.417
Even in a world like this,
he was really living.

00:11:37.250 --> 00:11:40.208
He wasn't losing a day
in the real world.

00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:42.583
He was gaining a day here.

00:11:43.542 --> 00:11:45.458
The one who taught me that

00:11:45.958 --> 00:11:47.500
was Kirito.

00:11:48.958 --> 00:11:51.500
When I began thinking of
him as I fell asleep,

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:53.458
I stopped having nightmares.

00:11:54.000 --> 00:11:56.542
I began to look forward
to seeing him.

00:11:57.208 --> 00:12:01.292
For the first time, I was glad
that I'd come here.

00:12:02.958 --> 00:12:05.000
For me, Kirito is

00:12:06.167 --> 00:12:08.500
the meaning of my two years here...

00:12:09.250 --> 00:12:10.750
And proof that I'm alive.

00:12:12.583 --> 00:12:14.875
The reason I put on the
NerveGear that day

00:12:15.667 --> 00:12:18.708
was so that I could meet him.

00:12:19.750 --> 00:12:23.792
I'm sure there's something
important to you here too.

00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:26.792
That's true...

00:12:27.125 --> 00:12:28.833
You're exactly right.

00:12:29.542 --> 00:12:31.500
Life isn't so bad.

00:12:32.125 --> 00:12:34.542
It's not so bad at all...

00:12:37.583 --> 00:12:41.042
There's nothing I can do
to help you.

00:12:41.042 --> 00:12:42.500
But good luck.

00:12:42.500 --> 00:12:45.125
Let's go fishing together again.

00:12:45.833 --> 00:12:47.083
We'll be going now.

00:12:50.542 --> 00:12:52.583
--Teleport: Grandzam.
--Teleport: Grandzam.

00:13:05.542 --> 00:13:06.417
"November 7, 2024"       "Floor 55: Grandzam"

00:13:06.417 --> 00:13:08.458
"November 7, 2024"       "Floor 55: Grandzam"
The recon team was wiped out?

00:13:09.208 --> 00:13:10.875
We sent in a 20-member party,

00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:15.375
taken from 5 different guilds,
to prepare for the boss fight.

00:13:15.708 --> 00:13:19.958
However, when the first 10
reached the center of the room

00:13:19.958 --> 00:13:24.333
and the boss appeared,
the entrance closed on them.

00:13:26.417 --> 00:13:28.792
An anti-crystal area.

00:13:28.792 --> 00:13:33.750
And five minutes or so later,
when the door finally opened...

00:13:35.083 --> 00:13:38.000
...nothing remained in the room.

00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:41.250
Neither the 10 men...
Nor any trace of the boss.

00:13:41.458 --> 00:13:42.542
That's crazy...

00:13:42.958 --> 00:13:46.542
But we still cannot give up
on clearing the game.

00:13:46.542 --> 00:13:49.792
We'll have to attack with
the largest group we can muster.

00:13:50.125 --> 00:13:52.167
We'll help out with that.

00:13:52.167 --> 00:13:56.750
But Asuna's safety
is my highest priority.

00:13:57.000 --> 00:13:58.875
If the situation gets risky,

00:13:58.875 --> 00:14:02.208
I will protect her over
the rest of the party.

00:14:02.625 --> 00:14:06.167
Someone who seeks to protect
something can be powerful indeed.

00:14:06.583 --> 00:14:08.708
I'm expecting a good fight.

00:14:13.583 --> 00:14:15.625
Another three hours, huh?

00:14:16.042 --> 00:14:17.333
What should we do?

00:14:20.875 --> 00:14:22.583
Hey, what's wrong?

00:14:24.542 --> 00:14:26.542
Don't get mad when I say this.

00:14:27.333 --> 00:14:29.125
Could you wait here

00:14:29.417 --> 00:14:32.708
instead of taking part
in today's boss fight?

00:14:34.958 --> 00:14:37.042
Why would you ask that?

00:14:37.333 --> 00:14:41.542
There's no telling what will happen
if we can't use teleport crystals.

00:14:42.750 --> 00:14:43.958
I'm scared.

00:14:44.500 --> 00:14:45.833
If anything happened to you...

00:14:45.833 --> 00:14:48.750
So you want to put
yourself in danger,

00:14:49.250 --> 00:14:52.000
while I wait here,
where it's safe?

00:14:55.417 --> 00:14:59.292
If you went and
didn't come back, I...

00:15:00.708 --> 00:15:01.917
would kill myself!

00:15:03.292 --> 00:15:05.208
I'd have no reason
to live anymore.

00:15:05.208 --> 00:15:07.458
And I'd never forgive myself
for just waiting around.

00:15:09.042 --> 00:15:10.292
I'm sorry...

00:15:10.292 --> 00:15:11.917
I'm losing my nerve.

00:15:12.292 --> 00:15:14.917
The truth is I just want
to run away with you.

00:15:15.958 --> 00:15:18.333
We don't have to return
to the real world.

00:15:18.875 --> 00:15:22.417
I want to live with you in that
house in the forest forever!

00:15:24.083 --> 00:15:25.792
It'd be nice if we could...

00:15:26.125 --> 00:15:29.333
We could be together
every day, forever.

00:15:32.083 --> 00:15:34.542
Kirito, have you ever considered

00:15:34.542 --> 00:15:37.500
what's happening
to our real bodies?

00:15:39.458 --> 00:15:43.250
When several weeks had passed
after the game's launch,

00:15:43.250 --> 00:15:47.833
there was an incident where most players
went offline for several hours, right?

00:15:48.417 --> 00:15:53.833
I think all of the players were being
moved to hospitals at that time.

00:15:54.667 --> 00:16:00.000
If our bodies are just barely being
kept alive on hospital beds,

00:16:00.375 --> 00:16:03.833
I can't imagine that we can
go on like that for long.

00:16:04.667 --> 00:16:05.958
In other words,

00:16:05.958 --> 00:16:09.458
whether we clear the game or not,

00:16:09.458 --> 00:16:12.917
we're on a time limit?

00:16:17.833 --> 00:16:19.625
I...

00:16:19.625 --> 00:16:23.542
I want to stay with you forever...

00:16:24.625 --> 00:16:26.833
I want us to date for real.

00:16:26.833 --> 00:16:29.417
To really get married...

00:16:29.417 --> 00:16:32.000
To get old together!

00:16:33.500 --> 00:16:34.750
So...

00:16:35.625 --> 00:16:36.667
So...

00:16:39.292 --> 00:16:43.208
For now, we have to fight, right?

00:16:46.417 --> 00:16:50.000
"Floor 75: Collinia Teleport Gate Plaza"

00:17:04.667 --> 00:17:05.667
Hey!

00:17:07.583 --> 00:17:10.417
Oh? You guys are coming too?

00:17:10.417 --> 00:17:13.083
What do you mean, "Oh?"

00:17:13.083 --> 00:17:16.458
I shut my shop down
to come and help.

00:17:16.708 --> 00:17:20.458
You don't even understand
my selfless desire to help?

00:17:20.458 --> 00:17:24.417
Then, we'll remove you
from the item drop list.

00:17:24.667 --> 00:17:26.917
I wouldn't take it that far...

00:17:42.333 --> 00:17:44.375
Corridor: open.

00:17:47.792 --> 00:17:50.000
Now then, let's go.

00:17:57.792 --> 00:18:00.417
There's a bad vibe in here,
don't you think?

00:18:00.417 --> 00:18:01.417
Yeah.

00:18:11.583 --> 00:18:13.083
Are you ready?

00:18:14.958 --> 00:18:19.958
The Knights of the Blood Oath will hold off
the boss attack in the vanguard.

00:18:19.958 --> 00:18:23.458
While we do, I'd like the rest of you
to discern its attack patterns,

00:18:23.458 --> 00:18:25.250
and be flexible with
your counterattacks.

00:18:26.083 --> 00:18:28.292
It will be a difficult battle,

00:18:28.292 --> 00:18:31.583
but I have faith that we can prevail.

00:18:32.250 --> 00:18:33.958
For our day of liberation!

00:18:48.042 --> 00:18:49.583
It'll be okay.

00:18:50.542 --> 00:18:52.917
I'll protect you, Kirito.

00:18:52.917 --> 00:18:56.292
So you protect me, okay?

00:18:57.000 --> 00:18:59.667
Yeah, I will for sure.

00:19:06.042 --> 00:19:07.167
Don't die.

00:19:07.750 --> 00:19:09.083
Same to you!

00:19:09.083 --> 00:19:13.542
I'm gonna make a fortune off today's
drops. I have no intention of dying.

00:19:16.333 --> 00:19:17.875
Attack!

00:19:42.792 --> 00:19:44.625
Nothing's happening...

00:19:51.958 --> 00:19:52.958
Above us!

00:19:58.000 --> 00:19:59.125
The Skull...

00:19:59.125 --> 00:20:00.417
...Reaper?

00:20:03.625 --> 00:20:04.667
Don't stay together!

00:20:04.667 --> 00:20:05.833
Stay away from it!

00:20:07.208 --> 00:20:08.250
This way!

00:20:08.917 --> 00:20:09.917
Run!

00:20:23.125 --> 00:20:25.000
W-With one hit?

00:20:25.375 --> 00:20:27.083
That's insane...

00:20:48.042 --> 00:20:50.833
We can't even get close to it!

00:20:52.750 --> 00:20:53.750
Get back!

00:20:56.875 --> 00:20:58.083
<i>It's too strong...</i>

00:21:04.125 --> 00:21:06.583
If we block together,
we can do this...

00:21:07.083 --> 00:21:08.667
We can do it!

00:21:08.667 --> 00:21:09.667
Okay...

00:21:11.417 --> 00:21:13.667
We'll deal with the scythes!

00:21:13.833 --> 00:21:16.292
Everyone else, attack from the sides!

00:21:17.083 --> 00:21:18.167
Let's go!

00:21:18.458 --> 00:21:19.458
Okay...

00:21:22.292 --> 00:21:24.000
Stay put!

00:21:29.958 --> 00:21:31.167
Damn it!

00:21:43.500 --> 00:21:44.583
Kirito!

00:21:45.333 --> 00:21:46.333
Yeah.

00:22:30.042 --> 00:22:41.542
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:41.875 --> 00:22:53.375
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.750 --> 00:22:59.292
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.625 --> 00:23:05.125
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.542 --> 00:23:10.542
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.875 --> 00:23:15.833
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.167 --> 00:23:22.667
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.000 --> 00:23:26.625
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.167 --> 00:23:33.875
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.208 --> 00:23:39.667
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:46.208
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:53.110
Next Time: "The End of the World."
